name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Super cool playground and huge. Thereâ€™s 2 part of play ground, one is for the younger kids and the other is for the older kids. Both is great and stimulating kidâ€™s sensory and body exercises. Prepare to apply bug repellent on your kids and you are good to go! Very nice place.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Good place for kids to play and spend their time. The park is well maintained. Water cooler to refill your water bottles are available. Washrooms are also well cared for. Highly recommended if you are around this vicinity.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: One of best park with Children play area. There are couple of play areas for kids in different age groups. Wild monkeys can spot on the park be careful while roaming.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: The park has the longest slides in Singapore,  there are a few other short slides and playground and a small zip line, kids can really enjoy playing at the park. Do remember to put on mosquito repellent to prevent mosquitoes bite. There are a few benches where parents can rest and wait while the kids are having fun. You can also find many wild and aggressive monkeys when you walk towards shiok garden. Do remember not to feed or disturb them. They are pretty agreesive and are not scare of human

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Good park with lots of shade. Has multiple play areas, for 2 - 5 years of age and 5 - 12 years of age. Slides, sandpit and climbing apparatus. The bathrooms are close by as well.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
This park is maintained in the very good shape, where you can find a super long slides and some other entertainment stuff in the playground,
To walk the whole round of this park will take around 5km, and can finish in an hour, good for weekend morning exercise.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: One of the best and biggest parks that catered for kids. Kudos to NParks for managing so well these parks and allowed us to enjoy open spaces with these facilities for free.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
One of the big & well develops park at north.
There have bike rental area , those if feeling tire on walk can consider rent bicycles.
Nice to come early morning , less crowd and monkeys everywhere :)

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Park comes with a long stretch of nature trail that is well kept. Could hardly hear the noise from the main road, but the vegetation is well grown to provide a surreal coverage that  beats some of the the nature trails. Yes, there are wild monkeys crawling around so please do pay attention. 2 carparks on each end (north/south), but the one on the south is really small so come earlier. This trail going north will lead you all the way to woodlands waterfront park just by crossing one road.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Nice park in the North connecting to Waterfront Park. Always full of kids and family on the weekends or PH. A nice natural mangrove full of flora and fauna beyond the pavement path.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: A fun park for kids,but please be careful of the monkeys. They were very aggressive taking people's food/bag/drink.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Fun and nice place to bring your little ones. From toddler to the young at heart adults, there are something for everyone. Personally i prefer to come in the evening as there is no heat from the sun and the playgrounds are cold to touch as opposed to morning or afternoon.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Fun playground for kids between 5-12 years old. The slides are the highlights of this playground. There is a carpark nearby.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: So much to offer for a park in comparison to other parks. Huge playground for both younger and older kids. Lots of wildlife around. May want to avoid weekends as the crowd can be a little stifling.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Very nice playground for kids of all ages. Big slides. Different ways of climbing up.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: We love this park a lot~ You just have to beware of the food in the stroller and bags, the monkeys are quite aggressive here ðŸ˜‚

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Great outdoor with those slides and swings. Also have a quiet nature walk around the well paved and shady path. Filled with wild birds chirping and critters singing. Also sighted a family of monkey foliage for their breakfast in the mangrove walk

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Great place for a trail walk. Suitable for all ages. Mostly flat trails. Can get hot and humid if you are planning to walk to the woodlands waterfront park as well so best bring a cap. Can get crowded during weekends but very peaceful on weekdays with regular joggers.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Great for family with young kids. Various playground for them to spend their time. Also a good place for a walk. The whole park is surrounded with trees - shady and cooling. Hungry for more ?  Woodlands Waterfront Park is just next to it ,offering a different  experience.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Excellent place for Kids play
Even parents will like it
Kids and adults will have good fun

Getting there from Woodlands Interchange:
Take 903 or 903M bus and get down at 2nd stop : Progen Building stopno. 46301
Opposite to the bus stop is the Park

Food: only one shop near the car park west entrance basement would say less or no option. Prefer bring own food and water

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: A large park with good amenities. Good for family outing, and the Mangrove Forest is educational for the kids! Highly recommend!

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
The place is good as you have read about. Spacious, lots of different kinds of slides and obstacles for your children to explore and enjoy. For every play area there are some benches for you to rest. Some of them are even sheltered.

When I went there on Sunday, there was a big family of monkeys. They are not afraid of humans, they can be quite aggressive. You are strongly encouraged to NOT feed them, nor take out your food/snacks in the presence of the monkeys. Stay calm if they are near, and calmly walk away. Don't be like that man that I saw, trying to scare the monkey away by swinging a bag at it. The monkey tried to snatch the bag away.

There's parking nearby, but limited slots.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: It has the most number of slides and is a child's dream playground. The nature park is tranquil with lots of shade. The mangrove walk is memorable. Be careful of monkeys though.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: A great place for parents with kids to spend a good 1hr+ at the slides alone. The playground is safe, though can be quite a lot of walking for the parents too. Awesome place and it is totally free.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Nice for morning and evening walks!  Often encounter monkeys and squirrels!  Occasionally, get to see interesting birds and other unexpected creatures too!

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Great place for kids!!! The flying fox is underrated and also great for adults!!!

Rope smelt like the sweat of a thousand men though....

Oh, and the rolling slide was closed when I went a couple of weeks ago, so do take note if you're headed there for that purpose.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: lovely park with engaging playground for children of all ages as well as a quiet park for the nature-lovers to just bask in greenery and nice walking paths

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
While the bigger kids are playing, it's a good place to clock your run. The trail goes 1 loop. Manage to clock 3km for 1 round.

Very well maintained park. Lots of greenery on the trails.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: I often go here for butterfly surveys but in my opinion, this park is perfect for family day outs. The playgrounds are huge and relatively inclusive, where the adults can freely explore with the kids. 10 mins walk or so to causeway point shopping mall where woodlands mrt is. So distance wise, is quite okay.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Slides,  slides and more slides. Exciting
Outdoor playground for kids.
Getting there : board 903 from woodlands bus Interchange and get down at Progen building (2 stops) or board 169 and get down at republic poly (2 stops)

Things to do:
1) Park is on hill terrain and designed like multi-tier theme and has two play areas one for juniors and the other for 5-10 years old.
2) biggest attraction is long metallic double barrel slides for kids to race.
3) slides at multiple levels and nets or climbing to move from one to another level.
4) personally my son liked roller-type slide.
5 ) wave shaped slide with nets to climb.
6) family swing, bridge with cargo net and many more.

Do take note to carry food for kids as only place to buy food and drinks is Cheers. Subway was closed on weekend.

I recommend this place for kids.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Not your usual playground. Best place to go to burn your kids energy. Minus one star because I witness monkeys attacking visitors for food. Went off early because I don't want them to snatch my bag.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: I have been reading so much about the slides and all here for some time. So I went there with huge expectation. I spent almost 1 hr 30 mins travelling to the park. But it was not what I had expected. Having said that, the play area is buzzing. Kids did enjoy. But I was hoping for some really extra ordinary experience.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: This park is amazing. It has a few playgrounds in it. Each of the playground is considerably big. The largest one has a really long slides from above the "hill". My kids really enjoy playing here

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Nice and pleasant  place for all level of people.  Big play ground is have fun for both kids and adults.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Very nice and large playground! The playgrounds stimulate all 5 senses of kids and is very fun. You can excercise there. You should go there to play!

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: A green, clean and spacious park. It's a perfect place for family outing especially, family with young children due to the big and diverse playgrounds in the park.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Nice place to walk. Not many people. U can take bus service number 903 from woodlands interchange and alight either at second or third stop depending which part youâ€™re heading. Its not a very long way in. But just be prepared with mosquito repellent since its mangrove area.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Went at night to avoid the heat of the day, and it was almost calm without too many kids around, but of course the area is not exactly well lit, but it was sufficiently lit lah.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Nicely forested Park with two linking bridges across the small streams. The canopy is high giving you a view out of the urban. It is well connected to waterfront Park.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: A good place for all ages to walk, jog and good for kids and family bonding.  Great playground and easy access parking. 2 carpark at 2 different entrances. Not a big park though.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Weekend always crowded.  Walking distance to Woodlands MRT station.  Just beside Republic Poly.  Park has two sections, one for kids below 7 years old and another section for bigger kids, big huge slide.

Due to covid some slide close.  Good to enjoy nature.  Still a great place to be than in shopping mall.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Itâ€™s really amazing feel when u walking into forest

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Wonderful play area with so many slides of different designs, that will make the kids spend fun-filled hours here! See if you can count 26 slides here - most number of slides in an outdoor playground in Singapore. The highlight is of course the tallest twin metal slides!

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: After modifications this park have many things where can spend time, specially for childrens can enjoy a lot here. And for running there is very good natural track.I always loved to run there, it's one of my favorite,there is also can see  mangrove three.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Free Park for enjoying with you kids. Come with your friends and enjoy a nice time togheter with the nature and avoid the smart phones please...

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Great place for the kids! Would recommend both parents are about as due to the length of slides it is difficult to get from one of the slide to the other or up and down the hill which ever one they are on. That aside there is lots to keep them occupied, not much shade and best to take plenty of water.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Amazed with so many slides in Admiralty Park Playground, 26 slides they say. My kids loved playing here, they were like machine that don't stop playing ðŸ˜„. There is also junior play area (below 5 yo). Amazingly, this park also wheel swing for people with wheel chair. Credit to the management. Don't forget to bring your water bottle. You can refill water from tap water in the toilet area next to the junior play. If you plan to visit Singapore with kids, admiralty park playground should be listed as one of place to visit.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: The fieat time that we went to thia park, there were a few slides that my kids could enjoy but the second time we went, it was disappointing coz some of the slides were under maintenance. When we checked online, there was no update on the maintenance, and it was showing 26 slides to enjoy, whereas there were only 2 or 3 slides that my 10 year old kid could enjoy.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Great place for kids to sweat it out.... Note that you need to apply sunscreen cos there is not much shade at the playground

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: A very nice place for your morning walk/exercise. The park is just a walking distance from Woodlands MRT station and you can also take bus 903 from Woodlands Bus interchange and align 2 stops later. You can start your walk from the Park entrance at the main entrance of Republic Polytechnic all the way to Admiralty Road and cross to Woodlands Waterfront Park. After your morning exercise, remember to stop by for breakfast at Marsiling Lane Hawker Center. There for plenty of good food awaiting for you.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: It was quite crowded on weekend, but my daughter enjoyed playing at the different slides available. There is also a smaller kids place area further up, if you have younger kids, they will enjoy it. Overall, we had an enjoyable time.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Great free park for kids of all ages, walking paths to see lots of wild life including some cute monkeys!

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Itâ€™s good place for family and Friends as itâ€™s quite fun place!!!!
Thereâ€™s a big playground with huge slide!!:)
Even the adult can enjoy together.

The park itself, itâ€™s also great place for walking!:) nice nature view and comfortable environment:)
Itâ€™s quite hot between 11:00-14:00 at the playground but thereâ€™s a shops and cafes at the Singapore institute of technology so that you gonna enjoy staying here;)!

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Pleasant undulating and mostly shady trails and park connector to walk or run. Lots of playgrounds.
So much to see and appreciate the natural flora, fauna, sungei cine river, and mangrove.
Toilet and easier parking at Admiralty Park North End car park where there is also a toilet, drinking water fountain, and drinks vending machines.
I used this as the starting point to cover Admiralty Park, Woodlands Waterfront park, and Marsiling Park..abt 11.5km.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: 'Best playground we've visited in Singapore'. Not my words but the words of our 4 year old daughter. Lots to do, shaded areas to sit, nature to look at and space to run around in. Great afternoon/evening out with the kids! 100% going back, we have no choice...

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: It's a good park to spend time with family who enjoys nature. A leisure walk to the mangrove swamp allows us to observe insects and plants. On our visit, there were also some macaques. After the walk, children can play in the two big playgrounds, for 5-12 yrs old and for smaller children

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: A lovely park with something to offer for almost everyone. Playgrounds for the younger children below 9 and the older ones till 12 years old. Quiet track to run in the tranquillity of nature was well.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: One of the better park especially the playground area for kids 5-12years old. Park with lots of shades from trees with large play area, slides, swings and tunnels. Enough benches with shelter for guardians to keep watchful eyes over their wards. Sands area abound so not recommended to wear socks and shoes. Playground areas are kids and wheelchair friendly. In fact, first time seen a swing for wheelchair. Free public toilet area provide a welcoming place to clean up as well as relief, even comes with 2 water coolers to hydrate oneself. As with all parks, watch out for the bicycles.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Many variety of slides and adults can play together with the children as well. The children loved the playground. The playground is also segregated into different children age group. It is advisable to visit early in the morning or evening time as the weather may get too hot.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Great Park for kids with its playground and slides. Good walk for adults through the forestry and mangrove areas

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Great outdoor playground. Really huge. Definitely a fun place for young kids. For children below 2yo, need full time supervision. Not easy for them to climb here. Some slides are too big and high for them. Got to prepare sunblock, lots of water to stay hydrated during hot weather. May have to bring along an umbrella just in case it rains. It's a bit of walking distance from carpark and not that much shelter.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Definitely the best park ever! So many slides here, every one of children loves here! Strongly recommend

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Self reminder to myself to come back next time. A great place for playing together as a family. Tons of fun activities for kids with many slides. For older people, we can spend time riding bikes around the park. Plus, there is a subway restaurant near it and a food court! The only con is that it is quite far if you are staying in Orchard area. But it is definitely worth the trip and it is free to play at the playground!

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Awesome place and food for young children below 12 . One big playground for kids to spend their time with swing, slides etc.. adult can also hike into the small tropical swamp land to see the nature. Hard to find such gem in the Urban city. Great place..

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: It's very lovely and clean park to hang out.. very nice park to bring kids to play.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Nice place for joining with nature wetland and listen sounds of birds ,squirrel and many other nature creatures ,just come and relax for your day !!

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: great park with lots of treeeesðŸ˜Œ

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: So far personally it is one of the best park I ever visited. spacious, cooling and scenic

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Children's Utopian Playground. They have zones for children older than 5 and young than 5. How thoughtful. You can easily find picnic places and replenish any drinks easily from the nearby Cheers.

Oh did I mention there's a buffet restaurant? Just make sure you call in to find out it's open or not when you visit.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Nice place for a stroll with many people having their morning exercise.

On one rare occasion, a family of otters were spotted

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Posted some info on Google Maps. Google making me post again. Can say pls refer there if it's your first time.its open to public no booking needed.

Bring cardboard for smoother slide. Bring cap, water, sanitizer.
Don't miss car park it's just 200m before the playground. Estimated playtime 40-60mins good enough.
Not much crowd even during school holidays. 4yo-14yo can play. Have a mini sand area. Have bridges. Can do some mini wall  climbing. Careful of the openings the fall can be quite steep.
Will go back again

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Playground is fun for kids, but certain playset needs to be relooked into as some items are not functioning as intended to be.

Overall, good place to walk or cycle to.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Definitely a jewel up north. Beside long green, circular and shadded trail with lots of wild lifes (e.g. birds, monkeys and lizard), it can also lead to Woodlands Waterfront Park for sunset and waterfront views (romatic if you are okay with the distinct sea side smell sometimes during hot days). The park is very well maintained, great for cyclists and joggers. The two large play grounds are suitable for kindergarten and primary school kids.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: A nice and easy trek in nature suitable for all ages. Enjoyed my trek from here to waterfront park.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Perfect for fun and adventure kids will surely love to play here

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Small park but with interesting and complex topographical features. The mangrove foliage with walk boards makes the park easy to explore. A river runs through the park with undulating miniature knolls on the one side; and on the other side pockets of wetland waters, enriching plant diversity. All this cramped into a tiny little corner  of northern Singapore. Only regret is to have all these beauty spoilt by the tones of debris from across the causeway.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Used to go to the park for my macro shoots. Park is now busier after the upgrade with boardwalk and slides playground. Can be quite busy on weekends.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: You can find a lot of slides for children all age. You can also find mangrove trees and the waterfront view where you can see Malaysia.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Great playgrounds for kids.  There are many playgrounds here for kids of various age. The unique thing here is that almost all the slides were built by taking the advantage of the up-and-down terrains.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Hidden Treasure of Woodlands. I love the Nature walk in the park and once you exit the park. You would see the park with the most Slides available and Republic Polytechnic. Sometimes we just need to Slow Down and Observe what is around us. We may realize that we might have missed out many things. As simple as the route From Your Home to Work, Camp or School

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
It's wonderful ðŸ¥° place for all ages.
But there is proper shelter if rain.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Very beautiful park ðŸ˜ðŸžï¸ and at the end across the road is  the Woodlands Waterfront which is a nice resting point with a breeze ðŸ˜Œ

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Such a gorgeous place. It's massive and has plenty of greens. The kids area is well kept and has a lot of Slides for all age groups.
.
The place is well maintained and top it all, it is free !

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: A nice play area for kids.. they will spend whole day also. It's a must place to visit with kids. They will ask to take again n again definitely. One drawback is, no food or beverages shops nearby. If you are planning to spend longer time better buy food n drinks from elsewhere before you go.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Very shady and cooling. The playground is great for kids and teenagers.  Adults would enjoy walking, jogging and cycling too.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: We love it. Plenty of slides and obstacles courses suitable for kids. A bit bump that the roller slide is close.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Cool place for kids to play! The play ground has long slides, rope nets for kids to execize, & just chill ! If driving the car park is too small very packed !

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Kids will love it as there are different slides to play. Quite a big park for family to relax and have some activities together. There is a Sakura buffet beside and its just beside Republic Polytechnic.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Nice park with playgrounds for kids, relatively new and clean too. There's also a buffet restaurant within walking distance located at park entrance.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Playground was ok and slides were quite safe although they seemed steep from the outside. Junior playground was closed so that's a damper. Take care of your belongings as the monkeys will come ransacking lol.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Excellent park with some of the best playgrounds I've seen. There are two main playgrounds, one that is suitable for ages 5-12, and another for 2-5. Both are excellent. I've also captured photospheres of each of the playgrounds so you can see how extensive it is. Worth a trip if you are in the area.

Nearby there is Republic Polytechnic, which has a food court and a Subway to grab food in case you get hungry.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: This park has got an state-of-the-art playground that features the longest tunnel slides, multiple slides that's integrated into a maze concept, swings with sand, flying fox/zipline, mini rock wall, suspension bridge, climbing nets, a junior playarea and loads more that provides hours and hours of fun.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: A very refreshing place for kids with many unique play units spread across the park. Also not to forgot have got some walking/cycling tracks.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Two hugh playground abt 100m from the west carpark. Nice place for morning walk but feel too dangerous for lady to go alone.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: I brought my 3yo nephew to admiralty park & we really really REALLY enjoyed ourselves. Thereâ€™s a section where itâ€™s meant for younger kids to play around in the sand pit & swings. So this picture shows the longest slide in the park, which is meant for 5-12yo. Do note not to let kids >5 run around on their own. I wish Iâ€™m a kid again.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
The Admiralty Park is next to the Republic Polytechnic campus. Is an urban park which is park connected to Woodlands Waterfront Park.

Roughly an hour closed to two hours for the return journey.

They have the longest slides in Singapore at the moment, worth to visit for family. Additional points, they have a swing for wheelchair access.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Within walking distance from Causeway Point (Woodlands MRT) and situated stone throw away from Republic Poly, the park is surrounded by lush vegetation. It has well-paved road for jogging and cycling.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Children so like this place, nice place for family bonding..

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Kids will be very happy at this new park in Singapore. The kids playground slides in this park is like a theme park, Universal studios rides for kids.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: nice and spacious and wasn't too crowded. the kids spent more than 2 hours just running up and down these slides and didn't have enough. there are smaller slides and simple walls for younger tots as well!

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Huge and fun playing area for kids! The park greenery and scenics is great for family bonding with outdoor activities!

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: The 2 super long slides were closed for maintenance on January 27 when we visited.  Most disappointing.  But overall this playground could rate a 5.  For ages 5 to 12.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Playground is great. The roller slides are currently under maintenance.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Excellent park - large, clean and fun. Minimum at 5 years old, based on the signs. A great workout for a kid and guaranteed to tire them out. The only downside is it's around Woodlands so pretty far out of town.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: It's a very spacious children park, lots of games , activities and so on. Kids will really love this place. Best holiday place for any kid.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Awesome slides... Haven't managed to try all 26 of them... Some will become very hot from being exposed to the sun. Wish there was more facilities there to cater to families with small kids

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: A very nice park with 26 different slides. A nice place for kids and adults. There are parking slots cafe and restaurant available.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Nice and spacious park with running track, water features, amenities and car park. Highlight of this park is the adventure play area for older kids and play area for younger kids and children with special needs. Best to go in the evening as it can get very hot. Located right next to Republic Polytechnic and Singapore Institute of Technology.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Nice Park,  asphalt and cemented path is good for families to walk.  Don't miss the boardwalk to bring closer view of the swamps and mangroves.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Small but lovely park, with the most comprehensive assortment of slides and climbs in a public playground in Singapore. Walking distance from Woodlands MRT station and Causeway Point.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Lovely park ðŸ‘.  Great for jogging and leisure walk. Has a big and adventurous playground for kidsðŸ¤©. Across the park, there's a scenic waterfront (Waterfront Park).

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
After renovation, it is good place for tracking and playing.
-----
We visited there last month and 50% of the park is under renovation at the moment.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Located near Woodlands MRT, and beside Republic Polytechnic, this park is conveniently accessible by residents of nearby neighborhood.

This park sport jogging track, cycling track, swings and slides and even mangroves. It is also home to squirrels and monkeys (feeding monkey is an offence). In between your trek, you will be greeted with shelters located in intervals to allow one to recuperate and seek shelter for the moment. Some shelters also have toilets and vending machine to buy drinks at their own convenience.

A good place to be if one needs to unwind. It breathes an aura of peace and tranquility that can be felt with nature.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Good playground for kids.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Marvelous place for kids to enjoy. Outdoor activities definitely better than video games.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Large three leveled playground with tunnel slides and small flying fox.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: A combination of nature and  children's playground, perfect place for a morning stroll

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: A park with lots of different slides for kids from 5-12 years old. There are also a lots of swings, climbing nets and sand ground for your kids to spend for new hours there. Good things is that there are many table and chair under the big trees with big shade which is good. A short and easy track way if you like nature (Lots of shade on the way) can connect to Woodland Waterfront Park. Not too many people which is good.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: It has 2 big playgrounds, 1 for below 5 yrs and 1 for above 5 yrs old.  Multiple slides, swings and sand pits around.  No food centres appear to be nearby so come prepared.  There is no shade so on a sunny day, you will need sunblock.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Good for children to play. If can build more around Singapore especially at Yio Chu Kang and Seletar Road Area

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: The park is very beautiful.Quite a distance from the MRT ~15 mins walk from woodlands mrt.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: My kid love the slides here! Just beware of occasional monkeys migration from the forest behind, can be nasty sometimes when they are hungry. This place offers one of the biggest play spaces that is complimentary and possibly playground with most number of slides!

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: What I like about this park is the nature trail that leads to Woodlands Waterfront Park. Came here on a weekday afternoon and it was not crowded.

name: Admiralty Park

great park in Singapore but under provisioned!

the park have a very high capacity but the amenities are just barely enough.

only 1 washroom,  no wash taps and washrooms next to the playgrounds, not enough seating areas for the elderly and family.

the car park slots are really not enough and it's like just for show.

not enough sun shades on the play ground itself and during a sunny day. the play ground equipment and the children will be like baking under the hot sun.

it's right next to republic polytechnic but the school blocks of the roads so no one can park in the school to access the admiralty park and playground.

what a waste of government efforts to be family friendly park.

i gave it a 3 stars is because the park is really nice to go but the supporting infrastructure is really bare and lousy.  it's like for show. dated jan 2020.

i hope the MP or government can quickly add in the missing items listed above.

should have these kind of play grounds at bishan park and tampines areas near IKEA

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Admiralty Park is a national park in the northern part of SG. It is 27 hectares in size made unique by its river following hilly terrain. There is a playground for kids, toilets & an exercise corner. There is also a restaurant in the park.

National Park works closely with neighbouring Republic Polytechnic, which is also the adopter of the park under the adopt-a-park scheme. One collaboration with them has been the Admiralty Park E-Guide, an online guide to the plants in the park produced by students from the School of Applied Science.

Admiralty Park is also has an amphitheater to hold performances. I enjoy nature hiking trail. and nature walks Wi-fi hotspots is available for visitors at certain locations around the park.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Admiralty park has gone a long way and is still under development to improve. It links parks from Republic Polytechnic all the way to Woodlands Waterfront. There are two huge kids playground on either side of the park, two halal eateries, and features gravel trails and mangrove walk. At the end of the park, there is a jetty facing Malaysia, where you can enjoy the sea breeze. The parks is also teeming with wildlife - you can easily spot squirrels and if you search long enough, monkeys as well. Woodlands residents love to take a brisk walk and jog here. Expect some crowd during peak hours. In terms of parking space, there are several options to choose from, right from RP to the open space carparks between the parks to the gantry carpark at Woodlands Waterfront. Perfect place to take the kids out.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Great place for the entire family to spend a half-day. It's easy to access, 2 or 3 stops from the woodlands MRT station. It has two parts; one "noisy" part is centered around two children playgrounds; the other consists of paved paths across quiet woods, good for jogging. In between the two parts there is a buffet restaurant (appearing closed due to Covid the day I am there) .

I have to say one of the playground, built against a slope, is very interesting and adventurous, suitable for teenagers and (when not crowded with kids) adults. You can climb up the slope and come down inside a tube shaped metal slide. The slope is quite deep,  and the top is probably 4-5 storey high above the ground. So sliding down is very exhilarating.

Jogging alone along the quiet woods could be a little scary in the evening, I guess. Basically you are running along 1-meter wide small path, and surrounded with tress with tropical smells. No visibility of any buildings and mains roads, although they are just near by. So if you really want to do it in the evening, go jogging with friends.

name: Admiralty Park

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:

There is a playground in the park with long slides. The play area makes use of the terrain to allow children (and adults) to climb about and slide down via a variety of slides. Families with children must make it a point to visit this park solely for the play area.

name: Admiralty Park

name: Admiralty Park

name: Admiralty Park
review_text: Nice park to visit if you're in the area, for a relaxing walk/run. There's playground, and you can also see people walking their dogs especially on weekend evenings.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
Admiralty Park is a park that is full of fresh air. The park is divided into two sections: one full of greenery and the other with a playground. The playground is new and has lots of slides with a "zipline" too, along with a wheelchair swing. I would say the experience there is exhilarating, and you would want to go back there for more.

The rest spots near the playground have also been newly renovated. Previously, the rest spots were made out of planks of wood with a sheet of aluminium (?) to act as a roof. Hornets and bees could be spotted regularly at the spot, along with ants. Now, the rest spots are covered entirely with concrete (?) and have been repainted, along with new tables and seats.

The slides at the playground can be pretty long, so a board with an advisory for adults not to play on the playground can be seen before you play. This is so that adults (who have a greater force of gravity due to their heavier weight) will not injure themselves after being thrown out of the slides due to high speeds. Unfortunately, people have been injured and have called the playground unsafe.

Also, the wheelchair swing is constantly abused by non-wheelchair users, and I can see why. Signs showing wheelchairs and a big board are installed next to or on the swing, but perhaps it is not prominent enough, and people always play happily on the swing, not knowing that it is not for them.

A public restroom is also available nearby, next to the buffet restaurant. The restroom is generally clean. The greenery found in the park includes a stream. The path is paved with concrete. Biking is allowed here, although some parts of the park have been closed temporarily. The park is also close to Woodlands Waterfront Park, but the entrance has also been closed temporarily.

The paths are usually well-paved, except for some cracks. There are bridges where you can gaze at a stream, and if you are lucky enough, you can spot a turtle, a fish or even a monitor lizard. Monkeys and mosquitoes are common in the park, so consume your food before you enter and put on sunblock and insect repellent. Fishing is not allowed here.

name: Admiralty Park

Such matters should be dealt with immediately by our National Parks and Recreation, jointly with Land and Transport Authority (LTA). Thank you for your attention.

name: Admiralty Park
review_text:
With a newly installed playground, this park has attracted more human traffic these days compared to the times when it was just a plain park with just a buffet restaurant, Sakura, as a main attraction.

The pond in the center has been either badly polluted or horribly maintained. At one end, streaks of oil can be seen floating on the water (nearer to the toilets).

The otters can be spotted occasionally at the river near the first wooden bridge after walking past the murky pond.

Nearer to the further end away from Ave 9, there used to be this tiny drain/stream with lots of fishes in it. But after a recent stroll to that place, the whole place was overgrown with weeds and the fishes seemed to have all died too. So sad to see a beautiful place with wildlife just die out due to neglect

review_text: Beautiful nature reserve park with natural trail on one side and road surface with a lot of tree cover on another. Feels like going into the forest for a walk. Avoid going on rainy days as tree branches may fall on the road side or the nature trail may have floods. Partially closed until Dec 2016 for upgrade works. Look up national parks website of singapore to know more.
